So my bf of 9 years wants a prenup as a non-negotiable condition to get married. We've been stuck in these negotiations for the past couple of years and that's why the unmarried situation. Even now, our only roadblock seems to be this prenup.
Background: I'm financially secure, have a good salary and prospects, own my own house, and have never needed any financial support from him. We've always split every expense down to the wire. He's on the same financial footing, net worth wise. Only i don't have any inheritances while he will inherit a bunch of property from his parents.
Initially I was okay with a prenup as he was paranoid about a family situation i have. So my brother owes investors in his business some multi-crores and has a few cases against him. I'm of course not involved in his business anyway, but my bf thinks or at leasts purports that he wants to secure himself from any liabilities that may arise from settling my brother's debts by his family members. i don't think that'll ever be the case.
But the prenup isn't just about securing himself against my family's liabilities but it also states how all our expenses will continue to be shared 50:50, how none us will get any alimony on divorce, and how the expenses of our future child if any would also be paid for by both partners, and no child support can be claimed at the time of divorce. I found these conditions fucked up as I don't think any financial equality post marriage and postchild is valid or fair, as i always contribute way more in the household work and taking care of pets/house so far and will be the same post marriage and post-child. He literally does no work in the house and everytime it comes up, he just asks me to "hire a fulltime help" instead.
